parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front suspension crossmember can cause the lower control arm bracket to separate, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vibrations while driving
uneven tire wear
pulling to one side while driving
shaking or wobbling of the vehicle
and loss of acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking power
vibrations while braking
and pulling to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the front end can cause uneven tire wear, vibrations while driving, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vibrations while driving
uneven tire wear
pulling to one side while driving
and shaking or wobbling of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame and Cross Member Rust Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust corrosion of the frame and cross member can cause the vehicle to lose structural integrity, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially catastrophic failures, especially when braking or driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates violently
the front end swerves
the brake pedal must be applied with extreme force to stop the vehicle
the front subframe bracket is fractured
the front cross member is completely rusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust failure of the idler arm can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents and potentially catastrophic failures.
symptoms: The right front idler arm has completely rusted away from the front cross member and is hanging loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fracture and fall-off of the door handles can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents if the door opens while driving.
symptoms: The inside plastic door handle on the rear driver and front passenger side have fractured and fallen off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brakes can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage properly
requiring the driver to pump the brakes to stop
unusual noises coming from the rear brakes
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and the ABS system kicks in unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brakes do not engage properly
unusual noises coming from the brakes
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ABS system kicks in unnecessarily
the brake pedal jerks back and forth
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake components, such as the rotor or brake wall, can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Unusual noises coming from the brakes
the brakes do not engage properly
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.
